metadata.name: Selene; Lunar deity
metadata.description:
"Divine Selene watched Endymion from on high,
and slid from heaven to earth; for passionate love
drew down the immortal stainless Queen of Night".

By myth, Selene's best known for her affair with the fair mortal Endymion, who, then fell in eternal sleep.

Selene is the Moon incarnate. Fierce, sensual and powerful - she's colder than the first frost, controls night as well as males' hearts. Eternal and agile, her beauty is dark and desirable.
